President Donald Trump addressed the NRA Leadership Forum in Atlanta, Georgia, where he thanked the organization for their support during his election campaign and pledged to protect the Second Amendment rights of American citizens. He also spoke about his administration's efforts to strengthen border security and combat illegal immigration, and highlighted the appointment of Justice Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court. Trump emphasized the importance of law and order, and promised to work with the NRA to promote responsible gun ownership and protect the rights of American hunters. He concluded by reaffirming his commitment to defending freedom and the Constitution.